window.docContents[150].resolve({"/Algebraic-Number-Theory/Number-fields-and-their-rings-of-integers/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Algebraic-Number-Theory--Number-fields-and-their-rings-of-integers--Ring-of-Integers":{"contents":"The ring of integers  of a number field  () is\nthe integral closure of  in : the subring of all elements of  that\nsatisfy a monic polynomial equation with integer coefficients. In mathlib \nis the type integralClosure ℤ K, equipped with its induced commutative-ring structure.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Algebraic Number Theory\u0009Number fields and their rings of integers","header":"3.1.2. Ring of Integers","id":"/Algebraic-Number-Theory/Number-fields-and-their-rings-of-integers/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Algebraic-Number-Theory--Number-fields-and-their-rings-of-integers--Ring-of-Integers"},"/Elementary-Number-Theory/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elementary-Number-Theory--Forthcoming-in-mathlib--Farey-Sequences":{"contents":"For a positive integer , the Farey sequence  is the set of reduced fractions\n with denominator , listed in increasing order. Two consecutive terms\n of  are Farey neighbours, characterised by the\ndeterminant identity\n\nand their mediant  is the fraction with smallest denominator strictly\nbetween them. The number of terms is\n\ncounting the reduced fractions of each denominator by Euler's totient ().PR #40246 develops Farey sequences, the mediant operation, and the neighbour theorem\n(the  characterisation of adjacency), the combinatorial backbone of the\nStern–Brocot tree and of best-approximation arguments. The neighbour identity is a Bézout\nrelation ().\nIn review — mathlib PR #40246.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Elementary Number Theory\u0009Forthcoming in mathlib","header":"1.7.2. Farey Sequences","id":"/Elementary-Number-Theory/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elementary-Number-Theory--Forthcoming-in-mathlib--Farey-Sequences"}});